76561198007335453,Not Recommended,418250,32411735,Posted: 14 June,all,Kumorigachi,"So , with what i've played so far this is my personal opinon.The game isn't bad. though as some other reviews have said there are definitely other games out there.the tech tree is okay as a novelty but it doesn't really have much in the way of ""random"" breakthroughs. it tells you exactly how long the tech will take to research and it shows it for all techs based on current amount of generated research points.the ship design is kinda lack luster. You have color coded slots where you can put things some things can go in a different colour coded slot but not all things.the ships are pretty much all locked in their appearance you don't really get much ability to change how they look.the race customization is minimal increase/decrease what your selected race is, or isn't good at. to do this you get a set number of race points adding a benefit takes them adding a penalty increases them. but in my opinon they don't matter and every race gets the exact same list of traits.and racial points. which isn't inherently a bad thing but aside from their lore and racial history/descriptions which are quite long. theres nothing that seperates them as different races outside of appearance which i find to be lame.the game plays like some of the more popular 4x games from the late 90s early 2,000s . the graphics are much the same.  the combat while offering a little freedom..suffers from the fact that its extremely slow paced atleast in the early stages. and no matter how far away you move your ships using the slight difference in speed..which is extremely slight..and so slow early on that it can be quite difficult to tell if your ""big"" ships are moving. the ships explosions , and damages to the ships aren't very detailed each ship/fighter gets a health bar once its depleted boom. but the ships fight at full strength till they explode. theres no component damaging , nothing to overly really draw in the more action oriented gamers.(edit i forgot to finish my initial thought which is ships will retreat directly through the enemy even if you give them speed to move fast enough in the opposite direction to get away. which means your ships will attempt to fly through over whelming fire power to escape being destroyed..even when they don't have to.)there aren't many story/plotlines that i seen there are some hidden things to 'explore'  like the troupe of searching asteroid, or debris fields an finding a bonus to tech, resources, or ships.I didn't have any bugs , or glitches in what i've played so far so the game seems quite stable. but for what it offers. it is not imo. worth 40$ so if you are thinking of getting it i would highly recommend waiting for a sale.Personally though with all the games currently on the market i wouldn't recommend this one. because for a game released in 2016 ,  and i know that 4x games are kind of a small portion of the market but they still should be made in as much quality as they can.the only thing that really stood out and appealed to me was the diplomacy which was quite wordy and had a lot of things you could 'say' to the other races. however the diplomacy is also kinda lacking because for all the words. its just the same bare bones diplomacy found in a lot of 4x games which saddens me. i like being the galactic empire who plays peace keeper and brow beats everyone through dipomacy this unfortunately doesn't really allow that.there is also no indication of people 'living' in the empire aside from the population numbers an the occassional ""invasion risk"" happiness modifer that pops up when your planet lacks ground forces to protect them no matter how powerful the space forces protecting them are. they still complain about not feeling secure without ground troops.also not really a game breaker or relavent to most. the game also doesn't give you the filling of running an empire. a lot of it is tedious and one thing that stood out to me was that the populations of planets for 'space' empires was quite small starting as the humans the population of earth was labelled as 110,000 and each colony ship only transported a thousand people each which from a realism stand point is a little on the silly side.I won't tell you whether you should buy it or not we all have our own personal tastes but if your looking for a game that has detailed diplomacy that makes you feel like your interactions matter this isn't really for you. if you're looking for epic space battles i don't think this has them either there just isn't enough detail in the battles to make them fun . if you're looking for a game with a decent amount of micromanagement, or macromanagement i don't feel either of those are added in a way that is 'fun.theres no way to simplify some of the tedious aspects such as producing fighters for carriers you have to manually load groups of fighters to the carrier. instead of simply ordering the fighters to be built specifically for the carriers so that you can save a bit of time.its a nice game and if this were 2000-2003 i would highly recommend it but for 2016-2017 its lack luster.but if you're looking for something thats kinda old school but is actually playable on modern systems then you might enjoy it."
