d at this period didn't touch me even close to this. Soul was no found. )  I am fan of Imperium Galactica 2, Pax Imperia, Master of Orion 1,2."
76561198004628852,Recommended,418250,22076971,"Posted: 26 March, 2016",all,W8taminute,"Polaris Sector is a space 4x game that I have been looking for in a long while.  Other games held my interest for a while but ultimately fell flat as I got bored with them.  Either those games were overly complex or too simple.  Polaris Sector seems to offer happy medium.  I've only played 5 hours at the time of this writing however this game is very addictive and is not too hard nor too easy.  There is a lot of depth in research, combat, production, ship design, etc.  I could go on but I'll save the details for when I have some more time under my belt.In short, I would take the negative reviews with some doubt.  I'm not sure why those reviewers hate on the game.  I'm a fairly critical individual but I'm having a hard time finding any faults with this game.Update (3.Apr 2016):  27 hours in at time of this writing.I have to say I still think this is a great game for the 4x space genre.  My first game as the humans ended in disaster and it wasn't because I lost to overwhelming firepower or spam fleets of doom.  It was because I overlooked the dangers of espionage and had no way to stop the enemy from sabotaging my mining.  The end result was that I quickly ran out of a key mineral type needed to sustain and build a fleet.  My ships wasted away because they no longer had access to the mineral they needed to keep the ships 'afloat'.  I was impressed and have started a new game as the Logans with this lesson learned.The research system is presentented in a refreshingly unique way.  It has been lauded by some and criticized by others.  If one takes the time to understand how the system works they will find that it's much more thought provoking than a typical static tech tree found in many strategy games.Ship design is a joy and is not a tedious chore.  The design system focuses only on the interesting aspects of ship design and abstracts the mundane such as life support, bridge room, etc.  Those components are assumed to be part of every ship and there is no need for the player to find precious space to install those pieces.  Instead the player is going to be faced with many interesting decisions about what components is needed for the ship in question.  The many possible combinations all layed out in a fairly easy to follwo format are impressive.  Ship design is almost a game within a game as you constantly need to assess problems in the galaxy and how to deal with them via a specific ship type.I experienced no mid or late game tedium.  There is always something to do in this game.  There is no busy work or mandatory tasks that must be performed manually that you find in many other games.  The ai does a good job managing your planets for you if you decide you don't want to micromanage them.  I like how you can also plan colonization automatically and let the ai handle settling in to that nice new planet you found.  In addition the ai does a fairly decent job at planning planetary ground invasions as well.  All in all I like having options to automate certain aspects of the game if I choose.That's all for now but I hope my feedback helps you decide one way or the other if you want to buy this game."
,Recommended,418250,22583291,"Posted: 23 April, 2016",all,freeliner,"Suprisingly fresh-looking 4x space strategy, compared to relatively all-the-same 4x titles published in the last couple of years.Finally:1. Relatively complex and deep tactical combat system, where every action means possible change of initiative and battle odds. Finally skill and tactical sense matters, and you can either lose your advantage if you make several mistakes, or you can win even against unfavorable odds if you make a few right decisions.2. The ship cost is very high - they are a long and expensive investment. So, like real battleships of our era - sometimes you make a new design for each new ship, and you feel that every single ship is unique and important for you. No faceless ship swarms here (except fighters and bombers swarms, of course).3. Long ship production times demand strategic planning. When you meet another race - will you try to build a couple of new colony ships to occupy good spots near their border, and leave them undefended, or will you build a couple of warships and risk losing possible colonization spot?4. Realistic colonization process, where new colonies initially are a liability to defend, and not a source of easy expansion.5. Research is unique in this game. Every single discovery you make is known beforehead, and appreciated, and quickly applied to ship designs after it is finally discovered.Cons:1. Due to long build and planning and exploration times game is not very fast-paced - so you have to be a bit meditative and patient while nothing else happens.All in all - a solid and interesting concept, at least after several gameplay hours."
