76561198064920926,Recommended,418250,31653954,Posted: 9 May,all,*****.10.efaferal,"This game is a gem.  A rough gem but a gem none-the-less.First off it is really just a 2x game.  There is no win by diplomacy/tech that I am aware of.  And, in fact diplomacy is broken.. There a a few ways to exploit the AI in order to avoid war pretty much indefinitely.However past that the game is excellent.  Better than excellent in fact.  The best feature of the game is the what has been coined 'Starship Tetris'.  While frustrating to some this is what creates the uniques natures of the various races.  But this also produces a highly un balanced strategic situation, to which some players are unable to adapt.  Each race has a different geometric layout for their ships and this, in turn, limits the placement of various equipment.  The result is that from the start certain races easily out-gun others.  This, in turn, forces the player to pursue a very specific research path in order to counter.  This game will frustrate player swho are used to RTS style build orders which can give you a dominant presence right from the start. Granted there are about 3 or 4 initial techs that are 'must have' from the beginning, however, after that you will need to commit to small, fast and stealthy or lots of guns until the middle game. Once you make it to the middle game the war becomes more grand strategy and less tactical.  However, by this point the weakness in the tactical AI become a bit too glaring.  The late game generally becomes a balance of defensive choke points and the player building the 'kill stack' of ships to knock down key planets.  then move the defensive bases to the new choke point, rinse and repeat.  This is really a 7 of 10 game, which is impressive for a one man show.  And he is currently performing a major upgrade!  so I must recommend support for this herculean effort and his continued interest in making a good game better.Final Score: 7/10Pros:- Tech system is semi-unique- Has a Star Wars MOD!- Ship designing creates variety, so players will have several purpose built ships.- Resource management requires planning (long term planning- AI does a good job managing planetary builds.- Good asymetrical tactical elements- Stealth and sabotage system is interesting and not too OPCons- Tech system is a bit obscured ( you will need to play through to find out where the necessary techs are )- Ship design is frustrating for the lazy player and limits species strategies with regard to conquest.- AI does a lousy job in tactical ship battles.Notes:Developer is in the process up creating an update which will address some of the logistical management shortcomings in the game, so I left those un addresed.-E"
