76561198031396231,Not Recommended,418250,22863811,"Posted: 8 May, 2016",all,Nalidus,"I'm going to preface my review by saying that there are some things that I like about this game.  However, there are more things that I dislike about it.Pros:1.  The starmap is quite beautiful and can be expansive.  It is also easy to understand at a glance.2.  The building automation AI for the worlds is pretty good.  I just wish there were more options to go with or a popup when a planet is done building with the automation.3.  The tech tree is vast and there is a lot to play with.  However, see ""Cons"" for further information.Cons:1.  The races are not that unique.  They feel fairly cookie-cutter due to easily customizing them when starting a game.  Truthfully, you could choose one race and give it all of the bonuses of another race.2.  The tech tree might be vast, but it's linear and extremely hard to really plan long-term as there is no real tree to look at.  It's linear in the fact that techs will be learned in the exact same order in every game you play unless you play with the sliders to research different things faster.  However, techs are still in the same line.  The tech tree is also almost impossible to look at ingame to see what to focus on what to get to a specific tech.  The devs provided a website with all the possible techs, but it's also difficult to navigate and plan with as well.3.  Here is the biggest problem with this game:  Racial ship balance.  Certain races have pathetically bad ships due to having either vastly lower number of slots, or having much higher build costs, or both.  Terrans are an example of the ""both"" category.  It's a really bad game design that needs to be fixed for this game really to have any long-lasting appeal and replayability.4.  And, finally, the AI is truly blood-thirsty.  Even peaceful races see military-weak races as targets for conquest."
