,Recommended,418250,22094350,"Posted: 27 March, 2016",all,Kurios,Pretty decent for a 4x
,Not Recommended,418250,22233437,"Posted: 4 April, 2016",all,Relden Calder,"At first glance, Polaris Sector appears to be a deep and meaningful strategy game, but ultimately it is neither deep nor a strategy game. This is not a 4X game, this is a tactical fleet simulator with a 4X veneer slapped on.Yes, you can expand and build an empire, but that empire has no meaning by itself, being defined solely by its ability to produce fleets of warships. Yes, you can micromanage your planets to your heart's content, but the problem is that planets only have four roles:1) Building ships.2) Producing resources to build ships.3) Researching new ship parts or ways to make resource extraction more efficient, so you can build more ships.4) Producing food to support the population that is used to power the facilities that perform the above three roles.You cannot, or at least, you should not, colonise planets for the sake of colonising planets. You should not grow your population as large as you can for the sake of having a large population. The game mechanics will penalise you if you do, because in order to do what the game wants you to do, you only need JUST ENOUGH population to man the factories, mines and farms that are all geared towards increasing your shipbuilding capacity.Diplomacy and technology are a joke, both existing solely as a means to further your ship production ambitions. There are NO technologies that perform any role beyond unlocking new ship weapons and modules, or a means to increase your production of physical resources.Can you research to improve your research ability? Nope. Can you unlock different forms of government with different empire-wide bonuses to production, diplomacy, morale or research? Nope. Just ship parts and mining equipment.This game is geared entirely towards designing and producing ships and enabling you to design and produce ships. The strategic layer could be removed and this game turned into a purely tactical game that allows you to begin battles from a Skirmish setup screen and nothing of value would be lost.If you're looking to buy this game because you want a good 4X game, DON'T. This is not a 4X game and it should not be advertised as such. I honestly regret spending money on this because of that one massive lie.If you're looking to buy this game because you want a good tactical fleet simulator with a anaemic strategic layer that only exists to make tactical battles happen, go right ahead, chief. Have fun. Someone should."
