76561197964686590,Recommended,418250,21984501,"Posted: 22 March, 2016",all,Speedy-Micro,"Initial Joke review:Game released right when I needed to get ready for an interview, delaying me: -2The game treats you like an adult, with alien babes from outer space that screw human men: +12A must buy for women with blue skin and boyfriends.10/10Actual review following lots of gameplay:Jokes aside, how often can you say, lore, tactical gameplay, ship design, research, and even AI and diplomacy are innovative and good?I thought games like this were a thing of the past with developers now trying to appeal to all age groups, favoring simplicity by cutting down challenge with intentional dumbbed down design. This game has restored my faith in games. It provides much wanted challenge albeit with a bit of a learning curve. (It'll feel new, not difficult)This game is something special. I implore you to buy it as a top pick from a long time lover of 4x games.If you are feeling frustrated with the new Master of Orion, this is the game that will make it all better again with no anticipation for the end of that games' early access. It's so much fun in my opinion. I love it, it's a classic for me on par with the feeling I got trying Master of Orion II as my first 4x strat game. It feels like a new and wonderful thing to be built upon for future titles, made by intelligent developers catering to adults. I am grateful that there are still people that treat their players like adults in game creation and all jokes aside, even with space babes, that space babe race has a great story that makes you ponder your own existence."
